object:25:27:25:27:A television murmurs softly to itself, showing a program no one in the room is really watching.:objects\tv.ogg
object:10:15:10:12:A wide sofa sags in the middle from years of children piling onto it at once.:objects\sofa.ogg
object:6:6:28:28:"Matron Elira says if you're going to help around here, start by using your eyes. The children leave needs lying in plain sight.":objects\npc.ogg
object:17:17:20:20:"If you're not busy, the little ones keep asking when supper is. They ask every ten minutes, but they mean it every time.":objects\npc.ogg
object:31:31:14:14:"Toma says the quiet room isn't haunted. Toma says that because he wants everyone else to stop daring him to go in.":objects\npc.ogg
object:22:22:8:8:"If someone ever fixes the emergency exit in the hall, maybe Matron will stop muttering at it under her breath.":objects\npc.ogg
object:4:8:8:10:A toy chest sits open, half full of carved animals, threadbare dolls, and a wooden soldier missing one arm.:objects\table.ogg
object:30:35:32:34:A long low shelf holds board games, chipped cups, and folded blankets for nights when everyone wants to stay in one room.:objects\bookshelf.ogg
door:40:40:20:20:data\maps\village.map:35:20:You step back outside the orphanage door.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:2:2:40:40:data\maps\orphanage_hall.map:10:1:You step from the common room into the orphanage hall.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:20:20:40:40:data\maps\orphanage_kitchen.map:10:1:Warm air and the smell of broth roll out from the kitchen.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
door:38:38:40:40:data\maps\orphanage_quiet_room.map:12:1:You step into the quiet room, where even the floorboards seem to behave themselves.:misk\doorsnd.ogg:misk\dooractivate1.ogg:true:false
